Business Brief -- Continental Cablevision Inc.:
   Preferred Shares to Be Sold
   To Fund for $400 Million
Continental, based in Boston, said the proceeds from the
financial arrangements will be used to reduce senior debt by
about $420 million.
   The preferred stock is convertible into Continental common
shares that represent a 19% ownership stake, the company
said. It added that Lester Pollack and Jonathan Kagan, top
Corporate Partners executives, will join Continental's board.